<!-- ═══ SECTION 2: REGIONS ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="regions">
  <div class="section-label" data-n="02">Regional Analysis</div>
  <h2 class="section-title reveal">Five worlds,<br><em>five cultures</em></h2>
  <p class="section-body reveal">Geography is destiny when it comes to drinking. Europe's <strong>cold climates and pub traditions</strong> push averages to 8.7L. The Americas split between beer-loving Central/South nations and spirit-heavy Caribbean islands. Asia's average is dragged down by large Muslim-majority populations. Africa surprises — higher than Asia, with beer culture in sub-Saharan countries like Namibia and Gabon.</p>

  <div id="region-cards" class="three-col" style="gap:16px;margin-bottom:56px"></div>

  <div class="two-col reveal">
    <div>
      <div class="chart-title chart-wrap">
